HEADWORD: Hippocrene
<hw>Hip"po*crene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/;
<grk>"i`ppos</grk> horse + <?/ a fountain.]</ety> <def>A fountain on
Mount Helicon in B⟦oe⟧otia, fabled to have burst forth when the ground
was struck by the hoof of Pegasus. Also, its waters, which were supposed
to impart poetic inspiration.</def> <rj><au>Keats.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

